Fan offers baseball player nachos after foul ball close call

Share
Tweet
What's This?
By Marcus Gilmer2019-04-26 14:01:38 UTC

Cincinnati Reds left fielder Jesse Winker turned down a friendly fan's offer of nachos after Winker made a stellar catch in front of the fan during Thursday night's game against the Atlanta Braves.

After Winker sprinted in from left field to catch a foul fly ball along the third base line, he made a move to take a bite from the fan's nachos. The fan was unfazed, playfully offering Winker a bite, but the player decided against it.

Which is probably for the best; as someone who has consumed gallons of stadium nacho cheese in my time, I can attest as to how it sits in your stomach like wet cement forever. Hard to run the bases full of all that cheese.
